The paper presents a solution that employs deep reinforcement learning (RL) to train a team of escorts to maintain payload safety while navigating alongside the payload. This involves coordination among multiple agents, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) category. The use of deep RL also suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper deals with navigation and obstacle avoidance, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) category. The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Finally, the paper deals with a specific application of defensive escort teams, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category.
